// The equipment approximately represent what an 40-alien team
// will have on battlescape. This is also the loot you get
// from auto-mission with 40 aliens. If there are n < 40 aliens,
// you get only n/40 of each item number, rounded down
// (the rounding down is the auto-mission penalty).
//
// Note that we describe the selection of weapon for aliens, but the same
// procedure is used for initial equipment of phalanx soldiers.
//
// Alien weapon assignment procedure, more or less (see inv_shared.c):
// For each alien, pick the following:
// 1. Get a primary weapon:
// 1a. Select a primary weapon:
//    There is 15% chance to select any primary weapon W in the equipment definition.
//    If no primary weapon is selected, the default selected weapon is the most expensive.
// 1b. See if this weapon is taken:
//    The selected weapon has a probability #W/40 to be taken
//    where #W is the number of W weapons listed in equipment.
// 1c. If W is not taken, then we go back to 1.a: another weapon X is selected,
//    but the default X weapon is the weapon which cost is just below W cost.
//    If there is no weapon cheaper than W, alien has no primary weapon.
// 1d. get the following number of ammo for each weapon separately:
//      (#ammo/#weapon) slightly randomly increased
//    with probability depending on the fractional part,
//    where #ammo and #weapon are the numbers of that particular
//    ammo and weapon in the equipment definition;
//    #ammo/#weapon should be greater than 1
//
// 2. Get a secondary weapon with reload (sidearms):
// 2a. Select a secondary weapon:
//    If primary weapon is a particle or normal damage weapon,
//    selected secondary weapon is the cheapest weapon.
//    Otherwise, it's the most expensive.
// 2b. See if this weapon is taken:
//    The selected weapon has a probability #S/40 to be taken
//    where #S is the number of S secondary weapons listed in equipment.
// 2c. If S is not taken, then we go back to 2.a: another weapon T is selected,
//    but the default T weapon is the weapon which cost is just below S cost
//    (or above if W primary weapon is a particle or normal damage weapon).
//    If there is no weapon fitting W, alien has no secondary weapon.
// 2d. If alien has a one-handed secondary weapon without primary weapon,
//    the is 30% chance that he get onather identical secondary weapon in
//    the other hand.
// 2e. get the following number of ammo for each weapon separately: see primary weapon
//
// 3. If alien has no weapon at this stage, there is 30% chance that we go back to 2.a
//    to increase the probability to get a secondary weapon.
//
// 4. Get misc items and secondary weapons without reload: (that includes kerrblades or plasblade)
// 4a. Select a misc items:
//    Select the most expensive item in list.
// 4b. See if the item is taken:
//    the selected item has a probability #I/40 to be taken (as long as it fits
//    in their hand / belt / holster).
//    if #I is greater than 40, then it automatically gets this item.
// 4c. If no item has been selected, then we try again with the item which cost
//    is just below I cost.
//
// 5. If alien has no primary nor secondary weapon at this stage, there is 30% chance
//    that we go back to 4.a to increase number of misc items.
//
// 6. Get an armour:
// 6a. Select an armour:
//    Select the most expensive armour in the equipment definition.
// 6b. See if this armour is taken:
//    The selected armour has a probability #A/40 to be taken
// 6c. If A is not taken, then we go back to 2.a: another weapon B is selected,
//    but the default B weapon is the weapon which cost is just below A cost
//    If there is no armour left, alien has no armour.
// 6d. There is a probability to retry to get an armour (go back to 6a), depending
//    on the result of step 1.b

// There is no problem if the number of assigned things
// is bigger than the total in equipment --- on average it is OK.
// For example, take 40-alien team, then 1 plasrifle
// makes it possible, though very unlikely, that each alien
// will get a rifle. Take a 30-alien team with 40 plasrifles,
// this guarantees that each alien will get a primary weapon;
// with 60 plasrifle_ammo, they will also get, on average, 1.5 ammo per alien.
// but with 2-alien team, 39 plasrifle gives only high probability
// that there will be at least 1 plasrifle in the team, no certainty.
// Each individual type of misc items and blades is assigned separately,
// so, e.g., 40 alienincgrenade and 40 plasmagrenade
// gives two grenades per alien, on average,
// while 40 plaspistol and 40 pbeampistol gives only 1 sidearm
// (so 20 plaspistol and 20 pbeampistol is a better idea in practice).

// there are 2 types of alien equipment :
// alien_workersS	or alien_soldiersS
//    S is any string (used to specify the equipment definition)
//    For a given stage, all equipment definition can be chosen with the same proability.
//    For each alien equipment, you must specifiy mininterest and maxinterest : the lower
//    and upper value of overall alieninterest that can use this equipment definition.
//    Equipment used will be picked randomly between all definition fitting overallinterest.
//    Note that all equipment definition must have different names.

